A Chief Magistrates’ Court sitting in Iyaganku, Oyo State, on Monday ordered that a 20-year-old bricklayer, Sodiq Raifu, who allegedly defiled a 16-year-old girl be remanded in Police custody, pending legal advice. Raifu, who resides in Olorunda – Aba area, Akobo, Ibadan, is charged with one count of defilement. Magistrate Titilayo Oyekanmi, who did not take Raifu’s plea, ordered that he be remanded pending legal advice from the Oyo State Directorate of Public Prosecution (DPP). Oyekanmi adjourned the matter until October 5, for mention, NAN reports. Earlier, the Prosecution Counsel, Insp. Sunday Ojeleye told the court that Raifu committed the offence on June 23, at about 7 p.m. Ojeleye alleged that Raifu ambushed the victim who was heading home after hawking and defiled her. He said that the victim’s father reported the matter at the Akobo Police Station, Ibadan and was later transferred to the State Criminal Investigation Department, Iyaganku. The offence, he said, contravened the provisions of Section 357 and is punishable under Section 358 of the Criminal Code Cap 38, Vol. II, Laws of Oyo State 2000